
teefs: Perform teefs operations

Usage:

Two sic flows are used to communicate with this container. The first flow
sets the current active file to which data will be written. If the file
already exists in teefs, its contents are returned.
The second flow (first flow + 1) writes contents to the active file.

cmtest cmd -f{FLOWID} {FILENAME}
    Set the current active file as FILENAME. If the file
    already exists, its contents are returned.
        FLOWID:   The flow id specified when loading the container
        FILENAME: The name of the file to be set as active

cmtest cmd -f{FLOWID + 1} {DATA}
    Write data to the current active file.
        FLOWID + 1: The flow id specified when loading the container, plus one
        DATA:       The data to be written to the current active file

# Examples

## Load the container

$ mwtest.py -c100 run teefs.img

## Set the current active file (file does not exist)

$ cmtest cmd -f100 test.txt
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 0 bytes OK

## Write data to the current active file

$ cmtest cmd -f101 data
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 0 bytes OK

## Set the current active file (file exists)

$ cmtest cmd -f100 test.txt
Sending data to CMRT via SIC...
...received 12 bytes OK
00000000: 01 00 00 00 04 00 00 00  64 61 74 61              |........data|

## Unload the container

$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
